@node Main "Appendix 2: Time Format Strings..."
@toc "FinalCalc:guide/main.guide/Main"
@font topaz.font 8
In FinalCalc, the way a time is shown is defined by the Time Format used to
display it.  The time format is a string made up of tokens that are used to
define how the time is displayed.


@{b}@{u}Time Format Tokens:@{ub}@{uu}

    h       One/two digit hour number
    hh      Two digit hour number
    hhh     The total number of hours, equaling   hour + (days * 24)
            (note that when used for a cell, if that cell has its Commas format
            on, sss will show commas in the number it shows.)

    m       One/two digit minute number
    mm      Two digit minute number
    mmm     Multi-digit minute number.   This is  minutes + (hours*60), i.e.
            the total number of minutes.
            (note that when used for a cell, if that cell has its Commas format
            on, sss will show commas in the number it shows.)

    s       One/two digit second number
    ss      Two digit second number
    sss     Multi-digit second number.   This is the total number of seconds.
            (note that when used for a cell, if that cell has its Commas format
            on, sss will show commas in the number it shows.)

    aa      am or pm
    a       a or p

    \\       Any letter following the back-slash will not be interpreted, and
            will be copied verbatim to the output format string.


    Examples:

    hh:mm:ss        13:51:10
    hh:mm           13:51
    hha             01p
    haa              1pm
    mmm.ss          831.10
    sss             49870



@{b}@{u}Time Format String requester:@{ub}@{uu}

The Time Format String requester comes up when you click on a [?] gadget
attached to a string gadget that expects a time string (e.g. "hh:mm:ss").

The requester shows you a list of the tokens you can use and what each does.
It allows you to select and paste the tokens right into the string, while
showing you 'live' what the resulting time string will look like.
@endnode
